					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">WhoaMan wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">NMI:<br />_if(timer) then do timer stuff<br />_get joypad input<br />_jump to state's NMI<br />_if(sprite update) update sprites<br />_if(scroll) set scroll<br />_rti</div>
<br />
<br />I do the joypad and timer code last (tho the timer first could be useful, if you want to check for and escape from a recursive NMI).
<br />
<br />Vblank time is short, so the rule I follow when I want to max out the PPU is to run all the video/sprite updates before anything that can take a variable amount of cpu cycles.  That includes checking for sprite updates, heheh, there's no harm in reuploading the same data every frame (actually it makes sense too, since it's DRAM and will die out if you leave it alone for too long).</div>

