			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In NeSnake 2 i only do VRAM updates and sprite updates in the NMI, then instead of doing other parts of the game engine in NMI, i increase a bunch of frame counters. The NMI quits, then the RESET loop notices the frame counters are &gt;= 1 and does further calculations (and sets up PPU buffers). I dont know, i got used to doing it like that. But i dont like the idea of another VBLANK ocurring while the previous NMI is still doing stuff. (which could happen in an all-NMI-based game). Other of those constant calculations Bregalad mentioned is the random number generator, and the joypad checking routine if i remember. I also do sound in RESET, which takes a deal of time.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

